DUBAI: Saudi Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman was spotted on Friday at a restaurant called Somewhere in AlUla, and fashion lovers on Twitter have once again gone wild over a vest that he wore. For the latest updates, follow us on Instagram @arabnews.lifestyle The crown prince championed the Italian brand Brunello Cucinelli’s zip-up gilet in white and beige. The straight hem vest, with a high neck, had two side-slit pockets. - إطلالة شتوية فخمه كفخامة ولي العهد ظهر بڤيست جاكيت من البراند الأيطالي Brunello Cucinelli pic.twitter.com/BkI4cL1jzM — ميشا FASHION (@fashion_shw) January 27, 2023 The vest retails for around $6,900 on luxury application FarFetch. Fans quickly started looking for websites selling the jacket at a lower price.  للأشخاص الي اعجبهم جاكيت ولي العهد محمد بن سلمان ولا هم قادرين عليه بسبب السعر هذا جاكيت مشابهه له وفيه عددة الألوان وجميع المقاسات وسعر ارخص
